{{SaoTomePrincipe-geo-stub}}

The '''geology of [[Abkhazia]]''' includes [[Neogene]] [[molasse]] deposits which are common along the coast. [[Paleogene]] [[greywacke]] and [[siltstone]] rocks run in a belt inshore into Georgia, while much of the northern and central areas of the country are underlain by [[Cretaceous]] and [[Jurassic]] rocks. The entire country is underlain by the suture left by the closing the [[Paleotethys Ocean]]. The region has asymmetric, isoclinal folding. <ref>{{cite book |author=Moores, E.M.; Fairbridge, Rhodes W.|year=1997|title=Encyclopedia of European & Asian Regional Geology|publisher=Springer|p=258}}</ref>

